OL,6,F"We can't really adjourn it so in the
OL,7,Fcircumstances I'm going to discharge
OL,8,Fyou.
OL,10,F"It's nothing to do with anything
OL,11,Fthat's happened with you but we are
OL,12,Fnot in a position to continue with
OL,13,Fthis trial and bring it to a
OL,14,Fconclusion.
OL,16,F"Your services are no longer required
OL,17,Fso you are free to go now. Thank you."
OL,19,FFollowing this, Baird was remanded
OL,20,Fback into custody ahead of a re-trial.
